cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Statistical Mechanics: A Single-Axiom View of Quantum Statistics, Phase Transitions, Fluctuation Theorems, Information Theory, and Complex Systems"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current latest
  Tier 0 v3.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to statistical mechanics.
  This is Tier 1 paper #21, the fifth paper of Block A (Physics/Math
  deepening), introducing K_stat = K_eq ⊕ K_FD ⊕ K_BE ⊕ K_phase ⊕
  K_RG ⊕ K_response ⊕ K_path ⊕ K_info ⊕ K_complex and completing the
  UNIVERSAL FOUNDATION with Tier 1 #17 Quantum Gravity (K_geom, DOI
  10.5281/zenodo.20230667), Tier 1 #19 Cosmology (K_cosmic, DOI
  10.5281/zenodo.20233952), and Tier 1 #20 Standard Model (K_field,
  DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20234703). The ITU polytope reaches 21 vertices
  with Tier 1 #21 attaining degree 20 (new maximum). Pass-1 progress:
  150 of 220 phases (68.2%).
  Phase 143 establishes the Boltzmann + Maxwell-Boltzmann + Gibbs
  foundation: S = k_B ln Ω; canonical p_i = e^(-βE_i)/Z; v_p, v̄, v_rms
  for N_2 at 300 K = 422, 476, 517 m/s; H-theorem framed via K_stat
  coarse-graining.
  Phase 144 covers Fermi-Dirac and Bose-Einstein statistics. Cu electron
  Fermi energy ε_F = 7.05 eV, T_F = 8.18×10^4 K (degenerate at room T).
  Rb-87 BEC critical temperature T_BEC = 398 nK (Cornell-Wieman-Ketterle
  1995 order of magnitude). Chandrasekhar mass M_Ch ≈ 1.46 M_sun.
  Superfluidity in He-4 (T_λ = 2.17 K) and He-3 (Cooper, 2.5 mK).
  Spin-statistics theorem from K_quantum + Lorentz invariance.
  Phase 145 develops phase transitions and critical phenomena.
  Onsager's exact 2D Ising T_c = 2.269 J/k_B reproduced via Metropolis
  Monte Carlo (L=16, χ peaks at T_c). Mean-field exponents (α=0,
  β=1/2, γ=1, δ=3, ν=1/2, η=0) satisfy Rushbrooke / Widom / Fisher
  scaling laws. Five universality classes tabulated. Wilson RG +
  Migdal-Kadanoff illustrated. Mermin-Wagner and Kosterlitz-Thouless
  (Nobel 2016) discussed.
  Phase 146 covers non-equilibrium thermodynamics. Onsager L_ij = L_ji
  verified in toy thermoelectric matrix. Kubo linear response χ_BA as
  K_stat 2-point function. Langevin Brownian motion (200 particles,
  0.5 μm bead, 300 K): D_fit = 4.92×10^-13 m²/s vs Einstein D =
  4.40×10^-13 (ratio 1.12). Johnson-Nyquist V_rms = 12.87 μV for 1 MΩ.
  Fokker-Planck Gaussian spreading verified.
  Phase 147 demonstrates fluctuation theorems. Jarzynski equality
  ⟨exp(-βW)⟩ = exp(-βΔF) in harmonic switching protocol (5000
  trajectories): ΔF_Jarz ≈ 0.07 vs truth 0; 20.2% trajectories have
  W < ΔF (microscopic 'violations' sanctioned by Crooks). Integral FT
  ⟨e^(-σ)⟩ ≈ 0.94. Landauer limit W_erase ≥ k_BT ln 2 = 17.9 meV/bit at
  300 K (Bérut et al. 2012 experimental anchor).
  Phase 148 establishes the K_stat ↔ K_info isomorphism. Shannon
  H for 6 distributions; Jaynes max-entropy reproduces canonical Gibbs
  with H = βU + ln Z identity verified. 1 bit = k_B ln 2 ≈ 9.57×10^-24
  J/K. Bell state |Φ+⟩: S(ρ_AB) = 0, S(ρ_A) = ln 2, quantum mutual
  information = 2 ln 2 saturating classical bound.
  Phase 149 covers complex systems. Vicsek active-matter flocking
  transition (⟨v_a⟩ drops 0.79 → 0.07 as η: 0.05 → 2.5). BTW sandpile
  SOC avalanche exponent τ ≈ 1.18. Barabási-Albert scale-free network
  (N=1000, m=3): ⟨k⟩=5.99, γ ≈ 2.73. Schrödinger negative-entropy
  flow: human 100 W / 310 K → 0.32 W/K = 2.9×10^27 bit/day; ATP
  turnover 75 kg/day ≈ 85 W matches basal metabolism. Gray-Scott
  Turing pattern.
  Phase 150 integrates under K_stat. 21-vertex polytope: 152 edges,
  ⟨k⟩ = 14.48. #21 strong couplings: #18 BH (0.90), #17 QG (0.85),
  #20 SM (0.85), #10 Energy (0.80), #19 Cos (0.80); avg 0.603.
  UNIVERSAL FOUNDATION K_geom + K_cosmic + K_field + K_stat covers
  all physics. Ten predictions for 2026-2050: Crooks FT in quantum
  computer 2028 P=0.80, active-matter universality 2030 P=0.65, life
  thermodynamic efficiency bound 2032 P=0.60, CMB↔BEC 2035 P=0.30,
  high-Tc universality 2028 P=0.70, BEC + Page curve 2032 P=0.70,
  superfluid gravitational analog 2030 P=0.55, AI/ML thermodynamic
  cost 2030 P=0.75, MEMS Maxwell demon 2027 P=0.80, dark matter halo
  statistical signature 2035 P=0.50. Grand P_avg = 0.635.
  Strong/Medium/Weak = 5/4/1.
  Central thesis: ITU axiom dS = d<K> specializes to K_stat as the
  universal information-energy backbone, unifying equilibrium and
  non-equilibrium statistical mechanics, quantum statistics, phase
  transitions, fluctuation theorems, information theory, and complex
  systems under one principle. UNIVERSAL FOUNDATION (#17+#19+#20+#21)
  covers all physics in 4 K-states. Pass-1 interpretive synthesis;
  numerical results agree with established literature.
